      <example>"Don't by an that orange. I bought an apple here once, and it was bad."&#xd;
&#xd;
Here, the speaker has concluded that all fruit in this store "is bad" from his one example. He could have derived several "rules", some more specific than others:&#xd;
* apples in this store are often bad&#xd;
* any fruit from this store is likely bad&#xd;
* everything in this store is flawed somehow</example>
